<div class="span-9">

  <div id="git-is">
    <h3>Git is...</h3>

    <p>Git is an <b>open source, distributed version control system</b>
    designed to handle everything from small to very large projects with 
    speed and efficiency.</p>

    <p><b>Every Git clone is a full-fledged repository</b> with complete history
    and full revision tracking capabilities, not dependent on network access
    or a central server. <b>Branching and merging are fast</b> and easy to do.</p>
    
    <p>Git is used for version control of files, much like tools such as
    <a href="http://www.selenic.com/mercurial/wiki/">Mercurial</a>,
    <a href="http://subversion.tigris.org/">Subversion</a>,
    <a href="http://www.nongnu.org/cvs/">CVS</a>,
    <a href="http://www.perforce.com/">Perforce</a>,
    <a href="http://www.bitkeeper.com/">Bitkeeper</a>,
    and <a href="http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/vs2005/aa718670.aspx">Visual SourceSafe</a>.  
    </p>
